# Release Report Output Format

When the user asks for release details/report/status/table:

- Run `src/run_release_mission.sh extract <branch[,...]> <count>` to fetch data.
- Return results in a tabular format by default.
- Keep **Release Title unique** per row.
- Include **Release Merged At** date/time (UTC).
- Include **Associated PRs** in the same cell with:
  - PR number
  - PR title
  - PR merged date/time (UTC)
- Prefer latest releases first (descending merged date).
- If user asks for "last N releases", show exactly N rows when available.
- Include associated PRs between current release and previous release window.
- Include reverted-release handling: do not consider reverted release until merged again.
- If no data is found, state that clearly and suggest increasing history limits.

## Default table columns

- Release Key
- Release Title
- Release Merged At (UTC)
- Associated PRs (Title + PR + Merged At UTC)

## Example Associated PR cell format

`#2375 Revert "...(#2318)" (2026-05-11T10:40:05Z); #2368 Added kernel changes ... (2026-05-06T08:49:46Z)`
